SUMMARY:Deadline: Filmfonds Wildcards (Documentary\, Fiction\, Animation)
DESCRIPTION:Talent prize for recently graduated bachelor filmmakers from a 
 Dutch film or art academy (documentary\, fiction or animation). Winners re
 ceive a small development purse to start a new short film\, and a much lar
 ger realisation budget once they have a producer attached. Annual round\; 
 deadline 7 July 2026 at 17:00.\n\nOrganisation: Nederlands Filmfonds\nLoca
 tion: Netherlands\nAward: Up to €3\,000 development to the maker + up to
  €50\,000 realisation (paid via attached producer)\nDuration: One-off ta
 lent prize per round\n\nMore: https://www.filmfonds.nl/subsidies/subsidie/
 filmfonds-wildcards-documentaire-fictie-en-animatie?utm_source=artificialn
 ouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
URL:https://www.filmfonds.nl/subsidies/subsidie/filmfonds-wildcards-documen
 taire-fictie-en-animatie?utm_source=artificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=
 referral
LOCATION:Netherlands
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:rtm-pitch-iffr-2026@artificialnouveau.github.io
DTSTAMP:20260720T142658Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260830
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260831
SUMMARY:Deadline: RTM Pitch 2026 (IFFR)
DESCRIPTION:Eighth edition of RTM Pitch\, IFFR's open call for Rotterdam fi
 lm talent. Submit a plan for a film between 5 and 20 minutes long\; a jury
  of film experts and IFFR programmers selects one filmmaker to receive EUR
  25\,000 to realise the film (with coaching and an IFFR 2028 premiere) and
  a runner-up to receive a EUR 5\,000 development budget co-funded by QISSA
 . All filmmakers are welcome\; this edition especially encourages genre fi
 lms (horror\, science fiction\, thriller\, fantasy) that use genre convent
 ions for a distinctive personal vision. Submit a written film plan (story\
 , setting\, team\, budget and financing\, cinematography vision\, with opt
 ional supporting material) or a video pitch of no more than three minutes 
 (Vimeo or YouTube link) via the application form. Deadline: Sunday 30 Augu
 st 2026\, 23:59 CEST.\n\nOrganisation: International Film Festival Rotterd
 am (IFFR)\nLocation: Rotterdam\, Netherlands\nAward: EUR 25\,000 for the w
 inner (EUR 20\,000 from the City of Rotterdam\, EUR 5\,000 from VEVAM Fond
 s) to realise the film\, plus tailored coaching and an IFFR premiere\; a r
 unner-up receives a EUR 5\,000 development budget co-funded by QISSA. No a
 pplication fee.\nDuration: Short film of 5 to 20 minutes\; winning film pr
 emieres during RTM Day at IFFR 2028\n\nMore: https://iffr.com/en/blog-rtm-
 pitch?utm_source=artificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
URL:https://iffr.com/en/blog-rtm-pitch?utm_source=artificialnouveaugrantdes
 k&utm_medium=referral
LOCATION:Rotterdam\, Netherlands
END:VEVENT
END:VCALENDAR
